<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- Live Entertainment Inc.:
   Revolving Credit Agreement
   With Two Banks Is Signed
</HL>
<DATE>
07/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5
</SO>
<CO>
   LVE
</CO>
<LP>
   Live Entertainment Inc., an entertainment software
supplier, distributor and retailer based in Van Nuys, Calif.,
said it signed a $100 million revolving credit agreement with
Credit Lyonnais Bank Nederland and Chemical Bank.
   The agreement, which runs through Jan. 2, 1992, is an
amendment to the company's $50 million credit facility with
Credit Lyonnais. Under the increased credit line, Credit
Lyonnais and Chemical will provide $60 million, and $40
million is expected to be provided by a group of U.S. and
overseas banks.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The credit line will be used for working capital by Live
Entertainment and its Live Home Video Inc. subsidiary.
</TEXT>
